ParallelChunk.en:
President-in-Office of the Council. - (PT) Mr President, Commissioner, ladies and gentlemen, Serbia naturally lies within the European space and we all recognise that, in recent years, it has been faced with major challenges;
in fact
more than this, with extremely difficult challenges due to its importance to the stability and development of the Western Balkan region.

We called on Croatia to make huge efforts and we asked Bosnia to do the same; 
          and
         these are the very same efforts that enabled us to rebuild Europe after the Second World War.
